Parade of Floats
Artist: Andrew Leister
2005

Parade of Floats is a procession of 16 sculptural "floats" along 5th Street between St. John and San Fernando Streets. These sculptures recall parades that are an expression of a community coming together in celebration. Each of these 16 floats are titled with themes that convey a vision of San Jose's historic and contemporary identity, as well as community priorities and values:

    
        
            Environment 
            Gold Rush
        
        
            Neighborhoods 
            High Technology
        
        
            Families  
            Innovation
        
        
            Arts & Creativity
            Diversity
        
        
            Education 
            Overcoming Adversity
        
        
            Trailblazers 
            Recreation
        
        
            Pueblo 
            Children
        
        
            Agriculture 
            Future
        
    


The pre-cast concrete bases for the floats are shaped as cars or chariots. The sculptures are ceramic tile over concrete and vary in shape and size. Seven of the themes have been developed in the form of columns, approximately 30 feet tall.


    
        
